The paper discusses traffic correlation attacks on Tor, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the importance of increasing AS-level diversity in the Tor network, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new Tor client, which involves software engineering (cs.SE).
